:name: XIAO nRF52840 wired split (T2)
:description: Two machines (central + peripheral), split-wired UARTs cross-connected via a hub.

# Console (banner, split-connect logs) is on each machine's uart0, exposed on
# its own TCP socket. The wired-split link is on each machine's uart1 (see
# overlays/split-wired-uart.overlay); both machines' uart1 are wired to the
# SAME Renode UART hub, making it a point-to-point link between the two
# emulated boards (see references/renode-notes.md for why a hub — not a
# server-socket terminal — is used here). This script only loads both ELFs
# and wires everything up; the harness calls `start` explicitly (over the
# monitor `-P` port) only after it has connected the console sockets, so no
# early boot-banner bytes are lost.

using sysbus

$central_bin?=@central.elf
$peripheral_bin?=@peripheral.elf
$central_console_port?=3465
$peripheral_console_port?=3466

emulation CreateUARTHub "split_link"

mach create "central"
machine LoadPlatformDescription @platforms/xiao_nrf52840.repl
emulation CreateServerSocketTerminal $central_console_port "central_console_term" false
connector Connect sysbus.uart0 central_console_term
connector Connect sysbus.uart1 split_link
sysbus LoadELF $central_bin

mach create "peripheral"
machine LoadPlatformDescription @platforms/xiao_nrf52840.repl
emulation CreateServerSocketTerminal $peripheral_console_port "peripheral_console_term" false
connector Connect sysbus.uart0 peripheral_console_term
connector Connect sysbus.uart1 split_link
sysbus LoadELF $peripheral_bin
